JOHANNESBURG, March 27 (Reuters) -    Below are comments from South African Reserve Bank Governor Gill Marcus at her latest decision on interest rates.

INFLATION "While the most recent inflation forecasts suggest marginal improvements in the medium term, upside risks to the inflation outlook persist despite the recent appreciation of the rand, which remains vulnerable to shifts in global risk sentiment and adverse domestic developments."